# Bootstrap 5 Standards

@https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.0

## Utility-First Approach

- Prefer Bootstrap utility classes (`d-flex`, `gap-3`, `p-3`, `mb-2`, `text-center`, `fw-bold`, etc.) over writing custom CSS/SCSS
- Only write custom styles when no Bootstrap utility exists for the need

## Layout

- Use the Bootstrap grid system: `container` / `container-fluid`, `row`, `col-*`
- Use responsive breakpoint variants (`col-sm-*`, `col-md-*`, `col-lg-*`, `col-xl-*`)
- Use `d-flex` and flex utilities for non-grid layouts

## Components

- Use Bootstrap component markup (cards, modals, navbars, dropdowns, alerts, badges, buttons, forms, etc.)
- Angular handles interactivity — do **not** rely on Bootstrap JS plugins or Popper.js
- No jQuery dependencies

## Responsive Design

- Design mobile-first, layering styles for larger breakpoints
- Use Bootstrap responsive display utilities (`d-none`, `d-md-block`, etc.)

## Spacing & Typography

- Use spacing scale: `m-*`, `p-*` (0–5 and `auto`)
- Use typography helpers: `fs-*`, `fw-*`, `text-*`, `lh-*`
